<quiz><question number="21">
        <prompt>What was the significance of the "watered stock" practice?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Artificially inflated stock values</option>
            <option letter="b">Improved company efficiency</option>
            <option letter="c">Increased railroad safety</option>
            <option letter="d">Protected investor interests</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Watered stock was the practice of artificially inflating stock values above their actual worth, allowing railroad companies to deceive investors and increase profits.</explanation>
