    <question number="22">
        <prompt>How did the development of refrigerated rail cars change the meat industry?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Enabled nationwide distribution of fresh meat</option>
            <option letter="b">Reduced meat consumption</option>
            <option letter="c">Increased local butcher shops</option>
            <option letter="d">Promoted vegetarianism</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Refrigerated rail cars allowed meat to be shipped long distances, leading to the rise of centralized meat-packing industries in cities like Chicago.</explanation>
